This was the last time that I was able to play alongside the legend that is Andrew Weatherall. 
I've known him, since 1988, when the first summer of love in the UK kicked in, he was definitely the stand out Dj. 
I got to play with him many times after that and he was always a pleasure to be around. One of my favorite times with him, was when I invited him to Brighton to play some tunes with me on a pirate radio called Festival Radio, and boy did we play some great tracks. Hearing this sad news, has left me with a heavy heart. He will be missed by thousands of people, especially me. RIP Andrew. Very sad indeed. üòìüôèüèΩ
